---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="How Many Days Until Christmas? Quick Date Calculator" description="Find out exactly how many days until Christmas with date calculation tips. Learn how to count days between any two dates for planning and countdowns." keywords="days until christmas, date calculator, countdown christmas, days between dates, date difference, christmas countdown, how many days">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Time</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">How Many Days Until Christmas? Quick Date Calculator</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 15, 2025 • 3 min read</p>

      <p>Whether you are planning holiday shopping, booking travel, or just building anticipation, knowing exactly how many days remain until December 25 helps with planning. But counting days between dates is useful far beyond Christmas.</p>

      <h2>Counting Days Between Dates</h2>
      <p>To calculate the number of days between any two dates, you need to account for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Different month lengths (28, 29, 30, or 31 days)</li>
        <li>Leap years (every 4 years, except century years, except every 400 years)</li>
        <li>Whether you count the start date, end date, or both</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Manual Calculation Method</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Count remaining days in the current month</li>
        <li>Add the total days of each complete month in between</li>
        <li>Add the days in the final month up to your target date</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> From July 15 to December 25:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Rest of July: 16 days</li>
        <li>August: 31 days</li>
        <li>September: 30 days</li>
        <li>October: 31 days</li>
        <li>November: 30 days</li>
        <li>December 1-25: 25 days</li>
        <li>Total: 163 days</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Days in Each Month (Quick Reference)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>January: 31 | February: 28 (29 in leap years) | March: 31</li>
        <li>April: 30 | May: 31 | June: 30</li>
        <li>July: 31 | August: 31 | September: 30</li>
        <li>October: 31 | November: 30 | December: 31</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Remember the rhyme: "Thirty days hath September, April, June, and November..."</p>

      <h2>Other Popular Countdowns</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>New Year's Day:</strong> Always 7 days after Christmas</li>
        <li><strong>Summer holidays:</strong> Varies by country and school district</li>
        <li><strong>Tax deadlines:</strong> April 15 (US), January 31 (UK self-assessment)</li>
        <li><strong>Your birthday:</strong> Use a date calculator for the exact count</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Date Calculators Are Useful</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Project deadlines:</strong> "How many working days until the launch?"</li>
        <li><strong>Pregnancy due dates:</strong> Count 280 days from last period</li>
        <li><strong>Lease/contract expirations:</strong> Know exactly when they end</li>
        <li><strong>Travel planning:</strong> "How many days is my trip?"</li>
        <li><strong>Event planning:</strong> Count backwards from the event to set milestones</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/tools/date-diff" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Date Calculator →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/tools/date-diff" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Tool →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
